==Classical Nahuatl==
===Alternative spellings===
*[[tequani]]
===Etymology===
'''[[te-#Classical_Nahuatl|tē-]]''' "someone; people" + '''[[tlacua#Classical_Nahuatl|-cuā-]]''' "eat" + '''[[-ni#Classical Nahuatl|-ni]]''' "habitually"
===Noun===
'''tēcuāni''' (''plural'' '''[[tecuanimeh|tēcuānimeh]]''')

# A [[man-eater]], a dangerous animal.
# A [[venomous]] animal.
# An [[unlucky]] [[day sign]].
